Done. Created `backend/src/services/token.service.ts` with the `markOrgTransactionProcessed` function that:

- Attempts to insert a `ProcessedOrgTransaction` record with the payment provider's `transactionId`
- Returns `true` on success (first arrival — caller should proceed with crediting tokens)
- Returns `false` on Prisma `P2002` unique constraint violation (already processed — caller should skip)
- Re-throws any other unexpected errors

This follows the exact pattern from `docs/token-credits-system.md` section 7, adapted for the org-level `ProcessedOrgTransaction` model. The unique constraint on `transactionId` ensures whichever path (client confirm or webhook) arrives first wins.
