**Endpoints:**

| Method | Path | Access | Description |
|--------|------|--------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/org` | Any authenticated user | Create org (caller becomes OWNER) |
| `GET` | `/org` | Any authenticated user | List user's organizations |
| `GET` | `/org/:orgId` | Member | Get org details + members |
| `PATCH` | `/org/:orgId` | ADMIN+ | Update org name/logo/website/billing |
| `DELETE` | `/org/:orgId` | OWNER only | Delete organization |
| `GET` | `/org/:orgId/members` | Member | List members |
| `POST` | `/org/:orgId/members` | ADMIN+ | Add member by email |
| `PATCH` | `/org/:orgId/members/:memberId` | ADMIN+ | Change member role (not OWNER) |
| `DELETE` | `/org/:orgId/members/:memberId` | ADMIN+ | Remove member (not OWNER) |
| `GET` | `/org/:orgId/events` | Member | List org's events |

**Key design decisions:**
- Role hierarchy enforced via `ORG_ROLE_RANK` (OWNER > ADMIN > EDITOR > VIEWER)
- Creating an org auto-creates the caller as OWNER and initializes a STARTER token balance
- OWNER role is protected — cannot be changed or removed via member endpoints
- Members can only be added with ADMIN/EDITOR/VIEWER roles (not OWNER)
- Follows existing patterns: Zod validation, `prisma` imports, `authMiddleware`, consistent error responses
