| `POST` | `/org/:orgId/events/:eventId/attendees/bulk` | Owner/Admin | Bulk add up to 200 attendees, returns per-entry results with summary |
| `PATCH` | `/org/:orgId/events/:eventId/attendees/:attendeeId` | Owner/Admin/Editor | Update eventRole and/or companyId |
| `DELETE` | `/org/:orgId/events/:eventId/attendees/:attendeeId` | Owner/Admin | Remove attendee from event |

**Key design decisions:**
- Follows the same patterns as `org-events.routes.ts` and `org.routes.ts` (middleware chain, event ownership verification, Zod validation)
- New users get a placeholder `firebaseUid` — auto-linked on first OTP login via the auth middleware's email fallback
- `shortCode` generation uses the same charset as `seed.ts` (excludes ambiguous chars), with 5-attempt retry
- Bulk endpoint is non-transactional per entry — partial success is reported rather than all-or-nothing, so one bad row doesn't block the rest
- 409 on duplicate enrollment instead of silently upserting
