### New file: `backend/src/routes/org/org-networking.routes.ts`

Three endpoints under `/api/v1/org/:orgId/events/:eventId/networking/`:

| Method | Path | Access | Purpose |
|--------|------|--------|---------|
| `GET` | `.../networking/config` | Owner, Admin, Editor, Viewer | Fetch networking config (merges saved config with defaults) |
| `PUT` | `.../networking/config` | Owner, Admin, Editor | Update networking config (partial merge — only sent fields are overwritten) |
| `GET` | `.../networking/slots/preview` | Owner, Admin, Editor, Viewer | Preview the full slot+break schedule grid based on current config |

### Configuration fields (all optional, with defaults matching current hardcoded values):

- **`slotDurationMinutes`** (default: 11) — meeting slot duration
- **`gapMinutes`** (default: 2) — gap between slots
- **`sessionStart` / `sessionEnd`** (default: 10:05–14:10) — overall session window
- **`slots`** — explicit array of `{timeStart, timeEnd}` bookable slots
- **`breaks`** — array of `{timeStart, timeEnd, label}` non-bookable breaks
- **`rolePairings`** — allowed `{requester, recipient}` role pairs (default: EXHIBITOR↔GUEST)
- **`roleBounds`** — per-role time windows (default: GUEST and EXHIBITOR both 10:05–14:10)
- **`autoConfirm`** (default: false) — whether meetings auto-confirm
- **`maxMeetingsPerUser`** — optional cap per user
- **`meetingRequestMessage`** (default: true) — whether requesters can attach a message

Config is stored in the `EventModule.config` JSON field for the `NETWORKING` module. The PUT endpoint validates all time ordering constraints and upserts the module record if it doesn't exist yet.
